      • isElementPresent

        public boolean isElementPresent()
        Checks if element is present in the html dom. An element that is present in the html dom does not mean it is visible. To check if element is visible, use getElement() to get WebElement and then invoke WebElement.isDisplayed().
        Returns:
        True if element is present, false otherwise.

      • getAttribute

        public String getAttribute(String attributeName)
        Get the value of a the given attribute of the element. Will return the current value, even if this has been modified after the page has been loaded. More exactly, this method will return the value of the given attribute, unless that attribute is not present, in which case the value of the property with the same name is returned. If neither value is set, null is returned. The "style" attribute is converted as best can be to a text representation with a trailing semi-colon. The following are deemed to be "boolean" attributes, and will return either "true" or null: async, autofocus, autoplay, checked, compact, complete, controls, declare, defaultchecked, defaultselected, defer, disabled, draggable, ended, formnovalidate, hidden, indeterminate, iscontenteditable, ismap, itemscope, loop, multiple, muted, nohref, noresize, noshade, novalidate, nowrap, open, paused, pubdate, readonly, required, reversed, scoped, seamless, seeking, selected, spellcheck, truespeed, willvalidate. Finally, the following commonly mis-capitalized attribute/property names are evaluated as expected: class, readonly
        Parameters:
        attributeName - the attribute name to get current value
        Returns:
        The attribute's current value or null if the value is not set.

      • getValue

        public String getValue()
        Gets the (whitespace-trimmed) value of an input field (or anything else with a value parameter). For checkbox/radio elements, the value will be "on" or "off" depending on whether the element is checked or not.
        Returns:
        the element value, or "on/off" for checkbox/radio elements
